President Obama has announced the appointment of Grant Colfax as the new Director of the Office of National AIDS Policy (ONAP). Colfax, a leading public health policy expert, will coordinate efforts to reduce HIV infections in the United States. ONAP focuses on prevention through education initiatives and helps coordinate HIV/AIDS care and treatment. Colfax will lead the administration's progress in providing care and treatment to those living with HIV/AIDS. ONAP works with other government agencies and international bodies to integrate America's response to the global pandemic with other prevention, care, and treatment efforts worldwide. Colfax, a graduate of Harvard Medical School, has previously worked in the San Francisco Department of Public Health, where he focused on HIV prevention and treatment interventions.